==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: butter-and-eggs
<hw>butter-and-eggs</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos><fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <def>a name given to several perennial
plants having showy flowers of two shades of yellow, or of yellow and
orange, such as <spn>Narcissus incomparabilis</spn> in Europe, and the
toadflax (<spn>Linaria vulgaris</spn>) in the United States; the latter
is a naturalized weed in North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> toadflax, wild snapdragon, devil's flax, Linaria
vulgaris.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Butterball</ent>⟦br⟧
